# Web UI (Mantine)

## Core Rules

- **Use Mantine components as the base** — extend them, don't create custom HTML elements
- **Use Mantine's sizing and spacing system** — don't hardcode dimensions
- Components should be **responsive** (Mantine responsive utilities) and **accessible**

## Color & Theme Access

**Prefer CSS variables for static styles:**

```css
background-color: var(--mantine-color-body);
color: var(--mantine-color-text);
color: var(--mantine-color-dimmed);
border-color: var(--mantine-color-border);
```

**For dark/light differences in CSS:**

```css
background-color: light-dark(var(--mantine-color-white), var(--mantine-color-dark-7));
```

**`theme.colors.*` is acceptable only for dynamic runtime color computation.**

## Button Guidelines

| Action | Color |
|---|---|
| Primary | Omit `color` prop (uses primary violet) |
| Destructive | `color="red"` |
| Secondary / Cancel | `color="gray"` or `variant="subtle"` |

## Data Access

- Use Supabase client from `src/utils/supabase/client.ts`
- Create utility functions in `src/utils/supabase/` for data operations
- Use hooks like `useRecords`, `useDailyDuration` when available
- Use Supabase real-time subscriptions for live updates when needed
